<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Spotlight on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/spotlight/</link><description>Recent content in Spotlight on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/spotlight/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] macOS Spotlight Not Indexing</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-spotlight-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-spotlight-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="macos-spotlight-not-indexing-fix"&gt;macOS Spotlight Not Indexing Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spotlight errors include incomplete search results, &amp;ldquo;Indexing&amp;rdquo; status that never completes, or Spotlight returning no results for known files. This affects file search and Quick Look previews.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spotlight maintains a metadata index of all files on the system using the &lt;code&gt;mds&lt;/code&gt; daemon. When indexing fails or stalls, search results become stale or empty. Common on external drives or after large file operations.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] macOS Spotlight Not Working — Indexing Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/spotlight-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/spotlight-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="spotlight-not-working--indexing-error"&gt;Spotlight Not Working — Indexing Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spotlight not working means the macOS search system either returns no results, returns incomplete results, or is stuck &amp;ldquo;Indexing.&amp;rdquo; Spotlight relies on a metadata index maintained by the &lt;code&gt;mds&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;mds_stores&lt;/code&gt; processes. When the index is corrupted or incomplete, search stops working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spotlight issues manifest as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Search returns no results or &amp;ldquo;No Results&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spotlight shows &amp;ldquo;Indexing&amp;rdquo; indefinitely in Spotlight preferences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;mdfind&lt;/code&gt; returns empty results from the terminal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some files are missing from search results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Search is extremely slow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spotlight index corrupted after disk errors or forced shutdown&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excluded folders in Spotlight privacy list&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;mds&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;mds_stores&lt;/code&gt; process crashed or is hung&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;APFS snapshot conflicts preventing index updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Third-party antivirus interfering with metadata service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix-spotlight-indexing-errors"&gt;How to Fix Spotlight Indexing Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-if-spotlight-is-enabled"&gt;1. Check if Spotlight is Enabled&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check if Spotlight is disabled&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mdutil -s /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Enable Spotlight if it&amp;#39;s off&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo mdutil -i on /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-rebuild-the-spotlight-index"&gt;2. Rebuild the Spotlight Index&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Delete the existing index and rebuild&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo mdutil -E /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Monitor the re-indexing process&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# This may take 30-60 minutes for large disks&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mdutil -s /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-check-and-remove-privacy-exclusions"&gt;3. Check and Remove Privacy Exclusions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# List excluded volumes&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mdutil -s
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Remove a volume from the exclusion list&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo mdutil -i on /Volumes/ExternalDrive
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or via System Settings → Siri &amp;amp; Spotlight → Spotlight Privacy&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-restart-the-metadata-server"&gt;4. Restart the Metadata Server&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Kill the metadata server to force restart&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo killall mds
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo killall mds_stores
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# They will restart automatically&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Monitor with:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ps aux | grep mds
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="5-check-for-spotlight-errors-in-console"&gt;5. Check for Spotlight Errors in Console&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Open Console.app → Search for &amp;#34;mds&amp;#34; or &amp;#34;Spotlight&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or from terminal:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;log show --predicate &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;process == &amp;#34;mds&amp;#34;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; --last 1h
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check system logs for index errors&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;log show --predicate &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;process == &amp;#34;mds_stores&amp;#34;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; --last 30m
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error commonly occurs when:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Spotlight Not Indexing Files Error on Mac</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-spotlight-error-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-spotlight-error-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="spotlight-not-indexing-files-error-on-mac"&gt;Spotlight Not Indexing Files Error on Mac&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spotlight search doesn&amp;rsquo;t find files, shows &amp;ldquo;Indexing&amp;rdquo; status indefinitely, or search results are incomplete/outdated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spotlight relies on the metadata server (mds) to index file contents. Indexing failures occur when the mds database is corrupted, the indexing process is stuck, or excluded folders prevent proper indexing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Corrupted Spotlight index database&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;mds process crashed or stuck&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Large files or folders overwhelming the indexer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Privacy settings excluding important folders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Third-party apps blocking indexing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disk errors preventing index writes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-indexing-status"&gt;Check Indexing Status&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check if mds is running&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ps aux | grep mds
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check indexing status&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mdls -name kMDItemContentType &amp;lt;file_path&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check Spotlight preferences&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mdutil -s /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="rebuild-spotlight-index"&gt;Rebuild Spotlight Index&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Disable Spotlight indexing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo mdutil -i off /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Delete existing index&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo mdutil -E /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Re-enable indexing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo mdutil -i on /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Force immediate reindex&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo mdutil -E /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-privacy-exclusions"&gt;Check Privacy Exclusions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# List excluded folders&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;defaults read com.apple.Spotlight orderedItems 2&amp;gt;/dev/null
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or check via System Settings &amp;gt; Siri &amp;amp; Spotlight &amp;gt; Spotlight Privacy&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="restart-mds-process"&gt;Restart mds Process&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Kill mds to force restart&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo killall mds
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# mds will automatically restart&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wait for reindexing to complete&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-permission-issues"&gt;Fix Permission Issues&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Reset Spotlight permissions&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo chmod -R /Users/$USER/Library/Metadata &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;755&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Rebuild in safe mode&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Restart Mac while holding Shift key&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-disk-health"&gt;Check Disk Health&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Verify disk integrity&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;diskutil verifyVolume /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Repair if needed&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;diskutil repairVolume /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/finder-error/"&gt;Finder Error&lt;/a&gt; — File browsing issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-macos-recovery-error/"&gt;macOS Recovery Error&lt;/a&gt; — Recovery mode&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-ssd-error-v2/"&gt;SSD Error&lt;/a&gt; — Storage issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>